---
---

<section
  id="learn"
  class="py-12 border-t border-[#ffffff10] text-[var(--white)]"
>
  <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
    <h2 class="text-lg text-[var(--sec)] mb-2 shiny-sec">The wisdom</h2>
    <h3 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-medium mb-8">
      Lessons from the Trenches
    </h3>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
      <div
        class="p-6 rounded-2xl border border-[var(--white-icon-tr)] bg-[#1414149c] hover:bg-[var(--white-icon-tr)] transition-all duration-300"
      >
        <h4 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">What Actually Works</h4>
        <ul class="space-y-3 text-[var(--white-icon)]">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-[var(--sec)] mt-1">✓</span>
            <span>Load test before you claim it's production-ready. K6 + Grafana will show you things code reviews never will.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-[var(--sec)] mt-1">✓</span>
            <span>Breaking things intentionally (HA testing, chaos) is how you earn the right to say your system is reliable.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-[var(--sec)] mt-1">✓</span>
            <span>Ctrl+Z is your best friend. git revert is second best. A good incident post-mortem is third.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-[var(--sec)] mt-1">✓</span>
            <span>Reading the error message actually solves it half the time. The other half, reading it twice does.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-[var(--sec)] mt-1">✓</span>
            <span>Taking a walk when you're stuck is more productive than staring at the screen. The bug will still be there when you get back, but somehow you'll know exactly where it is.</span>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div
        class="p-6 rounded-2xl border border-[var(--white-icon-tr)] bg-[#1414149c] hover:bg-[var(--white-icon-tr)] transition-all duration-300"
      >
        <h4 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">What Definitely Doesn't</h4>
        <ul class="space-y-3 text-[var(--white-icon)]">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-red-400 mt-1">✗</span>
            <span>"It works on my machine" — famous last words before every production incident I've ever seen.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-red-400 mt-1">✗</span>
            <span>Deploying directly to production on a Friday. Narrator: he did it. Once. Never again.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-red-400 mt-1">✗</span>
            <span>"I'll write tests later." (Narrator: They never did. The race condition found them first.)</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-red-400 mt-1">✗</span>
            <span>Skipping documentation because "the code is self-explanatory." Six months later, even you won't know what you meant.</span>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>
</section>
